## Next.js App Router Patterns

### File structure
```
app/
  layout.tsx          ŌåÉ Root layout (metadata, fonts, providers)
  page.tsx            ŌåÉ Home page
  globals.css         ŌåÉ Tailwind directives only
  api/
    [route]/
      route.ts        ŌåÉ API Route Handler
  [feature]/
    page.tsx
    _components/      ŌåÉ Feature-local components (prefixed _ = not a route)
components/
  ui/                 ŌåÉ shadcn/ui auto-generated components
  [shared].tsx        ŌåÉ Shared components
lib/
  utils.ts            ŌåÉ cn() helper and utilities
  [service].ts        ŌåÉ Business logic, API clients
types/
  index.ts            ŌåÉ Shared TypeScript types
```

### Server vs Client components
- **Default to Server Components** ŌĆō no `'use client'` unless you need: hooks, event listeners, browser APIs, or state.
- **Push `'use client'` down** ŌĆō wrap only the interactive part, not the whole page.
- **Data fetching** ŌĆō In Server Components, use `async/await` directly. In Client Components, use SWR or React Query.

```tsx
// Ō£ģ Good ŌĆō server component fetches data
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetchData()
  return <ClientWidget data={data} />
}

// ŌØī Bad ŌĆō fetching in client component unnecessarily
'use client'
export default function Page() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null)
  useEffect(() => { fetch(...).then(setData) }, [])
}
```

### Metadata
Always define metadata in `layout.tsx` or `page.tsx`:
```tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'App Name',
  description: 'Short description',
}
```

