## GitHub Repo Hygiene

### Must-have files
```
.gitignore          ŌåÉ Include: node_modules, .env, .next, .vercel
.env.example        ŌåÉ All env var keys with placeholder values (NO real secrets)
README.md           ŌåÉ Setup instructions, env vars needed, how to run
next.config.ts      ŌåÉ Typed config file
```

### `.gitignore` essentials
```
node_modules/
.next/
.env
.env.local
.vercel
*.log
```

### `.env.example` format
```
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/db

# Auth
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-secret-here
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000

# External APIs
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
```

### README structure
```md
## Setup
1. Clone repo
2. `npm install`
3. Copy `.env.example` ŌåÆ `.env.local` and fill values
4. `npm run dev`

## Deploy
Push to GitHub ŌåÆ connect to v0.dev
```

